<div style="width: 600px; max-height: 550px; overflow-x: auto;"><h1 class="green b_mar_ten">DECODING COMICON WITH BUDDY LEVY</h1>
	<p class="size11"><strong>Room: HALL A (611-614)</strong><em><br/>Start: 2:30PM<br/>End: 3:25PM</em></p><br/>
	<p class="rte">So just what is the big deal about comic conventions anyway? And why do they continue to be a worldwide<br>phenomenon after nearly 50 years? Join <b>Buddy Levy</b>, co-star of The History Channel's Brad Meltzer's Decoded, as he and a panel of convention experts take an insightful and entertaining look at what makes these shows resonate with both geek and mainstream audiences.<br><br>Buddy's guest panelists include <b>Kandrix Foong</b> (Convention Director, Calgary Expo), <b>Eric Trautmann</b> (Pro Comic Writer), <b>Phil Hester</b> (Pro Writer/Artist), <b>Mark Long</b> (Pro Video Game Developer) and <b>Bob Schreck </b>(E-i-C, Legendary Comics) and <b>Mike Robles</b> (Community Manager, Wizards of the Coast)!</p></div>